T17:44:17.000Z","msg":"marry"},{"pid":"396fa78307881368986c0b09d0778467f6ad1ce7","tid":958347,"uid":196924,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:19:19.000Z","msg":"其實好多地方都係講Happy Christmas<img src=\"/assets/faces/xm/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5de72358d9457eedcd204ba29a28ff9b514633be","tid":958347,"uid":192491,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:22:55.000Z","msg":"我用開jubilant"},{"pid":"9d631620f158cf287319a9302f6103c55e41cb32","tid":958347,"uid":68506,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:26:54.000Z","msg":"點解食完飯一定要屙屎?"},{"pid":"4c3fde6c66a884b8cc8f73e79dd004f3ddfb8338","tid":958347,"uid":29649,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:27:16.000Z","msg":"未聽過人用merry"},{"pid":"b473a471b9fdfb071bd4babffedb4c8949c5653d","tid":958347,"uid":55019,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:31:26.000Z","msg":"Thomas都得既"},{"pid":"7a468fc8d8e4a13eb1a68d06ec0b46cc6161a650","tid":958347,"uid":148076,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:33:41.000Z","msg":"「Merry Christmas！」今天是聖誕節，許多地方紛紛放上應景裝飾，讓大家感受濃濃過節氣氛。但你有沒有想過為何生日快樂是說Happy birthday；新年喊Happy new year，聖誕節卻是Merry Christmas而非Happy Christmas呢?<br />\n<br />\n據說Merry Christmas最早出現在1565年，一名海軍元帥寫在信裡的祝福。但Merry Christmas真正在英語圈崛起，則是拜英國大文豪狄更斯大力推廣所賜。<br />\n<br />\n1843年，狄更斯中篇小說《聖誕頌歌》發行後，立刻成為暢銷書，書中「Merry Christmas」一詞更迅速流傳開來。當時的商人便順勢推出印有Merry Christmas的聖誕卡，引發搶購潮，甚至賣到缺貨。從此之後，Merry Christmas的說法便隨著聖誕卡片傳遍全世界。<br />\n<br />\nHappy Christmas一詞雖不常見，但英國女王伊莉莎白二世卻經常使用Happy Christmas而不用Merry Christmas。英國女王的歷年聖誕致詞中，Merry Christmas僅出現在了1962年、1967年、1970年和1999年的四次致詞中，Happy Christmas則包攬了剩餘的年份。據說Merry是個出身窮苦的孩子，且在維多利亞時期，Merry一詞又含有「醉醺醺」之意，維多利亞人認為該詞有敗壞風俗的氣氛，因此將Merry改為較為中性的Happy。<br />\n<br />\n此外，除了聖誕節該是Merry Christmas還是Happy Christmas的疑惑外，美國也對於聖誕節該說Happy Holiday還是Merry Christmas爭論不休。無論如何，聖誕節來臨，大街小巷佈置的聖誕燈、裝飾，仍為寒冷的季節增添一份溫馨感。<br />\n<br />\n(中時電子報)"},{"pid":"204999221fd002a2edbe58c5eadb86aa9639a502","tid":958347,"uid":43231,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T18:53:22.000Z","msg":"叫開Mary<img src=\"/assets/faces/xm/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a15eb3324c8b99e9b4e7f440d9642f3067962651","tid":958347,"uid":152047,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T20:21:50.000Z","msg":"叫開 Merry Merry Christmas"},{"pid":"2bd5509d3592d19ff3dad102214086c4c154651b","tid":958347,"uid":33668,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"a15eb3324c8b99e9b4e7f440d9642f3067962651","tid":958347,"uid":152047,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T20:21:50.000Z","msg":"叫開 Merry Merry Christmas"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T20:24:13.000Z","msg":"叫開 lonely ~lonely christmas"},{"pid":"d3291775943e3e822c42fdd383d5426e868ff787","tid":958347,"uid":100760,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T20:24:31.000Z","msg":"要扮英國正宗皇室英文一定係講happy christmas"},{"pid":"94293450fb1d53a6597ba9b7d69fe867931c61e2","tid":958347,"uid":15758,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T20:25:02.000Z","msg":"叫開very"},{"pid":"166e7d872bc9919c54ef66e8bc0ccd2393ed9aa4","tid":958347,"uid":29606,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T23:24:41.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"e93e5ca4acfaf14b27afde868cfc4e31b8199624","tid":958347,"uid":211316,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-12-27T23:48:35.000Z","msg":"今年英女王按照傳統發表聖誕文告，有「心水清」的讀者發現，女王祝聖誕快樂時，用「Happy Christmas」而非「Merry Christmas」。<br />\n<br />\n「Happy Christmas」並不常見，英國人以至英女王卻常用「Happy Christmas」。<br />\n<br />\n在歷年聖誕文告中，女王僅在1962年、1967年、1970年和1999年用過「Merry Christmas」。<br />\n<br />\n資料顯示，「Merry Christmas」可追溯至1565年，在一名海軍將領的信件中出現; 但「Merry Christmas」真正成為英語的流行用法，應起源於大文豪狄更斯1843年的中篇小說《聖誕頌歌》。<br />\n<br />\n「Merry」一字在維多利亞女王時期 --- 亦即英國人形成聖誕傳統的時期 --- 被廣泛使用，及後逐漸被「Happy」取代。有英語專家指，「Merry」形容人的醉態，也使人聯想到狄更斯小說中的不良人物，屬於低下階層的用語。<br />\n<br />\n英王喬治五世在首個電台聖誕文告中採用「Happy」，等同宣示「Happy」是皇室認可較妥當的字眼。因此，更多英國人因此採用「Happy」而棄「Merry」。<br />\n<br />\n此外，也有研究批評英女王的聖誕文告幾乎千篇一律，多年下來用了逾4萬個字，但只有大約4000個字從未重覆，近年較多加入基督教元素，包括在文告中提及耶穌。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.sbs.com.au/yourlanguage/cantonese/zh-hant/article/2016/12/26/wei-he-ying-nu-wang-yong-happy-qi-merry?language=zh-hant\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sbs.com.au%2Fyourlanguage%2Fcantonese%2Fzh-hant%2Farticle%2F2016%2F12%2F26%2Fwei-he-ying-nu-wang-yong-happy-qi-merry%3Flanguage%3Dzh-hant&d=2Fzy6X4tYhsMvz%2B9IN6yg%2F6YfqAiA4jm3R2Vm1010vU%3D&h=785f6192\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.sbs.com.au/yourlanguage/cantonese/zh-hant/article/2016/12/26/wei-he-ying-nu-wang-yong-happy-qi-merry?language=zh-hant</a>"}]}